OL,6,F"Therefore you can't sit on your hands
OL,7,Fon this one."
OL,9,FThis is not the first time that
OL,10,FWestminster has been asked to
OL,11,Fintervene. The Chief Constable Jon
OL,12,FBoutcher reached out to the Prime
OL,13,FMinister last year. He was criticised
OL,14,Ffor going above the Executive to make
OL,15,Fa plea over finances.
OL,17,FLast week, the Policing Board's Chair
OL,18,Fwrote to the Secretary of State
OL,19,Fappealing for a round table meeting
OL,20,Fover how Legacy PSNI cases are funded.
